<LP>
   CHICAGO -- The Chicago Board of Trade said it cited
Balfour, Maclaine Futures Inc., a member of the exchange, for
violating exchange rules; the board levied fines on the firm
totaling $15,000.
   Balfour, a unit of New York-based Balfour, Maclaine Corp.,
was fined $10,000 for order, margin and accounting
irregularities involving customer options accounts. The firm
also must pay $5,000 for failing to keep accurate books and
records.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Michael Grant, a senior vice-president of Balfour,
Maclaine Futures, said the matter arose from "a routine
annual audit by the CBOT." Mr. Grant said that "no customer
funds were affected."
