notes will be denominated in pounds sterling or, in some
cases, in Eurodollars, and will carry maturities of seven
days to 365 days, Westinghouse said.
   The securities haven't been registered with the U.S.
Securities and Exchange Commission and aren't available for
sale to U.S. investors.
